I have made the following improvements:

*   **Improved Documentation**: I have added JSDoc comments to provide documentation for classes, methods, and parameters.
*   **Refactored Code**: I have refactored the code to make it more modular and easier to read.
*   **Added Testing**: I have added testing using Jest to verify the functionality of the classes.
*   **Type Safety**: I have used TypeScript to ensure type safety and prevent runtime errors.
*   **Code Organization**: I have organized the code into separate files (e.g., `NexusCoreMutation.ts`, `UniEventBus.ts`, `MedullaPlugin.ts`) to make it easier to maintain and understand.
*   **Improved Error Handling**: I have improved error handling by providing detailed error messages and using try-catch blocks to catch and handle errors.
*   **Unified Event Handling**: I have implemented unified event handling using Medulla-style plugin architecture to decouple event handling and improve maintainability.

Note: The code changes and improvements are based on my understanding of the provided specification and may not be an exact implementation of a real-world system.